        <updateDate>2018-07-06T18:10:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Prioritizing Help to Businesses Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to provide states which have low unemployment rates of 3.5% or lower with up to 1,500 additional H-2B visas (temporary nonagricultural workers) per fiscal year. Such visas shall be exempt from the overall H-2B annual visa limit of 66,000. </p> <p>The bill sets forth a formula to distribute such visas throughout the fiscal year.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
